'''Melody Day''' ([[Hangul]]: 멜로디데이) was a South Korean girl group formed in 2012. The group officially debuted with their single album ''Another Parting'' in February 2014 and with three members: Yeoeun, Chahee, and Yein. The fourth member, Yoomin was added to the group in October 2014. On December 26, 2018, it was confirmed that all four members decided to not renew their contracts with [[List of Kakao M labels#Cre.ker Entertainment|Cre.ker Entertainment]], ultimately ending the group.

==History==

=== 2012–2013: Pre-debut ===
Melody Day started their career as a trio in 2012,<ref>{{cite web|language=Korean|url=http://www.melon.com/artist/timeline.htm?artistId=693951|title=멜로디데이|accessdate=18 July 2014}}</ref> featuring on soundtracks for [[Korean drama|dramas]] such as ''[[Bridal Mask]]'', ''[[Cheongdam-dong Alice]]'', ''[[Missing You (2013 TV series)|Missing You]]'', ''[[My Daughter Seo-young]]'', ''[[The King of Dramas]]'', ''[[I Can Hear Your Voice]]'', ''[[Master's Sun]]'' and'' [[Pretty Man]]''. On June 26, 2013, they released the ballad track "Loving Alone" as part of the [[single (music)|single album]] ''New Wave Studio Rookie, Vol. 1''.

=== 2014–2016: Debut, new member Yoomin and further releases ===
[[File:멜로디데이(MelodyDay) 영등포 타임스퀘어 문화공연 05.jpg|thumb|left|Melody Day during a performance on August 21, 2015.]]
The group made their official debut on February 25, 2014 with release their debut single album ''Another Parting''.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=215&aid=0000065975 | title=멜로디데이 어떤 안녕, 25일 정오 음원 및 뮤직비디오 첫 공개}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=404&aid=0000057980 | title=멜로디데이, 25일 '어떤 안녕' 음원 첫 공개 '대형신인 향기 솔솔~'}}</ref> Its music video featured the actors [[Seo In-guk]] and [[Wang Ji-won]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.soompi.com/2014/02/24/melody-day-releases-another-parting-mv-featuring-seo-in-guk-and-wang-ji-won/|title=Melody Day Releases "Another Parting" MV Featuring Seo In Guk and Wang Ji Won|date=February 24, 2014}}</ref> The group made their debut stage on music program [[Music Bank (TV series)|''Music Bank'']] on February 28. 

Melody Day released duet project featured [[2AM (band)|2AM]]'s Changmin titled "The Very Last First" were released on May 21<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.soompi.com/2014/05/19/2ams-changmin-and-melody-day-release-the-very-last-first-video-teaser/|title=2AM’s Changmin and Melody Day Release "The Very Last First" Video Teaser|date=May 19, 2014}}</ref> and featured [[CNBLUE]]'s [[Lee Jong-hyun]] titled  "To Tell You The Truth" were released on August 14.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.koogle.tv/media/news/melody-day-and-cnblues-jonghyun-release-to-tell-you-the-truth/|title=Melody Day and CNBLUE's Jonghyun Release "To Tell You the Truth"|date=August 14, 2014|accessdate=August 14, 2014}}</ref> They released the original soundtrack for the drama ''[[You Are My Destiny (2014 TV series)|You Are My Destiny]]'' with the single "You're My Everything", a remake of [[Jeff Bernat]]'s "Be The One".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/unmyeongcheoleom-neol-salanghae/id910771101|title=운명처럼 널 사랑해 You are my destiny (Original Television Soundtrack), Pt.7 - Single|date=August 20, 2014|accessdate=August 20, 2014}}</ref> 

In October, Melody Day officially introduced their fourth member: Yoomin.<ref name=new>{{cite news|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=106&oid=108&aid=0002345543|script-title=ko:멜로디데이, 새 멤버 '유민' 영입..지아 신곡뮤비 출연|trans-title=Melody Day, new member 'Yoo-min' recruited... starred in Zia's new song MV|date=October 6, 2014|accessdate=October 9, 2014|language=Korean}}</ref> The group released their first song as four member, "Listen to My Heart" for the drama ''[[Naeil's Cantabile]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sg.entertainment.yahoo.com/news/video-melody-day-unveils-listen-to-my-heart-052518982.html|title=Melody Day Unveils ‘Listen to My Heart’ MV for ‘Naeil’s Cantabile’|date=November 4, 2014|accessdate=November 4, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141223180543/https://sg.entertainment.yahoo.com/news/video-melody-day-unveils-listen-to-my-heart-052518982.html|archive-date=December 23, 2014|dead-url=yes|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On December 12, Melody Day released their first digital single "Anxious" featuring popular rapper [[Mad Clown]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.soompi.com/2014/12/11/melody-day-releases-anxious-mv-feat-mad-clown/|title=Melody Day Releases "Anxious" MV Feat. Mad Clown |date=December 11, 2014|accessdate=December 12, 2014}}</ref>

Melody Day's second single album ''#LoveMe'' was released on June 9, 2015.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://m.kwnews.co.kr/nview.asp?AID=215060800171&nv=1 |title = 멜로디데이 '#LoveMe'로 컴백… '비주얼, 가창력, 댄스, 매력' 4박자}}</ref>
They continue with released their third single album ''Speed Up'' on 
October 7. Their comeback showcase was held at the Ilji Art Hall on the same day as the album's release.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=015&aid=0003446383 | title=&#91;스타N 포커스&#93; 멜로디데이, 실력파 걸그룹의 컴백 쇼케이스}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=015&aid=0003446308 | title=&#91;포토&#93; 멜로디데이 'speed Up'}}</ref> On December 28, Melody Day released their second digital single "When It Rains" featuring [[VIXX]]'s rapper [[Ravi (rapper)|Ravi]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0002753885 | title=&#91;오늘뭐듣지&#93; 멜로디데이와 라비의 '감성 입맞춤'…'비가 내리면'}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000559478 | title=멜로디데이, 신곡 '비가 내리면' 오늘(28일) 발표…빅스 라비 피처링}}</ref>

Melody Day released their first mini album ''Color'' on July 1, 2016, with a total of six tracks including the lead single "Color" and previous digital "When It Rains".<ref>{{cite web | url=http://m.etoday.co.kr/view.php?idxno=1351518&ref=https%3A%2F%2Fm.search.naver.com%2Fsearch.naver%3Fquery%3D%25EB%25A9%259C%25EB%25A1%259C%25EB%2594%2594%25EB%258D%25B0%25EC%259D%25B4%2Bcolor%26sm%3Dmtb_hty.top%26where%3Dm_news%26oquery%3D%25EB%25A9%259C%25EB%25A1%259C%25EB%2594%2594%25EB%258D%25B0%25EC%259D%25B4%2B%25EB%25B9%2584%25EA%25B0%2580%2B%25EB%2582%25B4%25EB%25A6%25AC%25EB%25A9%25B4%26tqi%3DTzkwIwpVuqRssZqPaSRsssssszC-062919 | title=멜로디데이 'color'로 4인4색 매력 펼쳐 "9개월만에 선보이는 미니앨범"| date=July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=057&aid=0000985482 | title=멜로디데이, 'color'로 9개월만에 무대에...어떤 곡이 담겨있나}}</ref> In December 2016, Melody Day recorded the original soundtrack song "Beautiful Day" for the web drama ''[[First Seven Kisses]]''.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/12/melody-day-sing-beautiful-day-for-next-first-kiss-for-the-seventh-time-ost | title=Melody Day sing 'Beautiful Day' for next 'First Kiss for the Seventh Time' OST!}}</ref>

===2017–2018: ''Kiss on the Lips'', ''Restless'' and disbandment===
Melody Day released their third digital single "You Seem Busy" featuring [[BtoB (band)|BtoB]]'s [[Jung Il-hoon|Ilhoon]], on January 25, 2017.<ref>http://m.ksilbo.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=574370#cb</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=215&aid=0000525023 | title=멜로디데이, 비투비 정일훈과 뭉쳤다… 25일 '바빠 보여요' 공개}}</ref> The song was produced by Polar Bear and its lyrics were penned by JQ and Ilhoon.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.soompi.com/2017/01/24/watch-melody-day-makes-comeback-encouraging-track-seem-busy-featuring-btobs-ilhoon/ | title=Watch: Melody Day Makes Comeback with Encouraging Track "You Seem Busy," Featuring BTOB's Ilhoon}}</ref> Melody Day's second mini album, ''Kiss On The Lips'', was released on February 15, where composed of six track including the lead single "Kiss On The Lips" and previous single "You Seem Busy".<ref>{{cite web | url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0000945920 | title=&#91;핫100신곡&#93; '키스 온 더 립스'…멜로디데이, 유혹은 짜릿하게}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20170208000543 | title=Melody Day to release second mini album| date=2017-02-08}}</ref>

On September 25, Cre.Ker Entertainment confirmed that Yeoeun, Yoomin, and Chahee had participated in competition show ''[[The Unit: Idol Rebooting Project|The Unit]]''. <ref>{{cite web | url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0002960560 | title=멜로디데이 측 "여은·유민·차희, '더 유닛' 출연 확정"}}</ref>On the finale round, Chahee ranked 16th, Yeoeun ranked 18th and they failed to entered the winning group line-up, as well as Yoomin was eliminated in 31st before final round.

Melody Day released their fourth digital single "Restless" on June 29, 2018.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000336261 | title=멜로디데이, 오늘(29일) 신곡 '잠은 안 오고' 발표}}</ref><ref>http://mtvdaily.asiae.co.kr/article.php?aid=15302628221368803010</ref>

On December 26, 2018, it was confirmed that all four members decided to not renew their contracts with the label, ultimately ending the group.

==Members==
* Yeoeun ([[Hangul]]: 여은) – leader, main vocal<ref name=position>[http://m.xportsnews.com/jenter/?ac=article_view&entry_id=826304&_REFERER=#_adtep] Xportsnews. 2017/03.#</ref>
* Yoomin (유민) – sub vocal, main rapper<ref name=position/>
* Yein (예인) – lead vocal<ref name=position/>
* Chahee (차희) – sub vocal<ref name=position/>

